						<summary>

						<p>This is also a Veṭṭeḻuttu inscription dated in the * +1+1st year of a king whose name is lost. It records a gift of 100 sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple at Tirutturutti a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> in Aṇḍa-nāḍu, by a lady named Kuṉṟañjundari of Koṟṟavāyil-śēri in Māḍa-Madirai.</p>						

						</summary>
